told me about. Brought 'em in one at a time.

361
00:26:53,405 --> 00:26:56,033
- They all came up with the same story.
- Oh, yeah? What story's that?

362
00:26:56,116 --> 00:26:58,702
Well, they never deny
following you.

363
00:26:58,785 --> 00:27:00,704
They say they drove up
on the accident...

364
00:27:00,787 --> 00:27:03,248
called 911 and never left
until help arrived.

365
00:27:03,332 --> 00:27:05,667
Detective, that's bullshit.
You hear me?

366
00:27:05,751 --> 00:27:09,338
Come on, man.
Give me a break, will ya?

367
00:27:09,421 --> 00:27:11,340
I'm just tellin' you what I got.

368
00:27:11,423 --> 00:27:14,718
Until I find someone who saw
somethin' different, that's all I have.

369
00:27:14,801 --> 00:27:17,387
What about the, uh, other driver?

370
00:27:19,056 --> 00:27:22,643
He died late last night.
He never regained consciousness.

371
00:27:24,645 --> 00:27:29,399
I'm sorry, Bo. But listen, if there's
a witness out there, I'm gonna find him.

372
00:27:29,483 --> 00:27:31,610
Believe me.

373
00:27:31,735 --> 00:27:33,570
I'm all over this one, Bo.

374
00:27:34,821 --> 00:27:36,740
I appreciate it.

375
00:27:43,580 --> 00:27:45,457
The victim died, Bo.

376
00:27:45,582 --> 00:27:47,835
What now?

377
00:27:52,422 --> 00:27:54,800
Did you mean to kill him, Bo?
Nice driving.

378
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:03,517
- Stellar Agency. Please hold.
- That's for pickup, Sara.

379
00:28:03,642 --> 00:28:08,105
Bo, taking these paparazzi to court
is only gonna cause more headlines.

380
00:28:08,230 --> 00:28:11,108
Let it go. We've got bigger
problems to deal with.

381
00:28:11,191 --> 00:28:15,445
The studio says we get back to work or they
will be forced to shut down the picture.

382
00:28:15,529 --> 00:28:18,490
Five weeks, Bo. They're losing
a tremendous amount of money.

383
00:28:18,615 --> 00:28:22,035
The bond company is now threatening to
go after you. And your production company.

384
00:28:22,161 --> 00:28:24,830
Technically, you weren't hurt.

385
00:28:26,081 --> 00:28:29,585
- What'd you say?
- Uh, Bo, you're upset.

386
00:28:32,421 --> 00:28:34,631
You don't know shit.

387
00:28:36,633 --> 00:28:38,510
I'm sorry.

388
00:28:45,350 --> 00:28:47,436
So, what do you want us to do, Bo?

389
00:29:20,219 --> 00:29:22,095
And that's a cut. Excellent!

390
00:29:22,221 --> 00:29:24,723
- Well done.

391
00:29:24,848 --> 00:29:27,768
Whoo. Way to do it.
Way to do it.

392
00:29:27,893 --> 00:29:29,520
- You all right?
- Yeah.

393
00:29:29,603 --> 00:29:31,522
All right.
That's a wrap, everybody.

394
00:29:31,605 --> 00:29:33,607
We'll pick it up here
tomorrow morning.

395
00:29:33,732 --> 00:29:35,859
What you got, Jay?

396
00:29:35,943 --> 00:29:37,903
Just a bunch of crap.

397
00:29:40,030 --> 00:29:43,242
Oh, man.
"Laramie's wife on drugs."

398
00:29:44,409 --> 00:29:46,328
"Star too busy to notice."

399
00:29:46,411 --> 00:29:49,289
Mr. Laramie?
I'm Reggie, Aegis Security.

400
00:29:49,414 --> 00:29:52,376
- Hey, Reggie.
- The studio sent me to keep an eye on things.

401
00:29:52,501 --> 00:29:55,546
I'll be on set for the rest of the show.

402
00:29:57,089 --> 00:29:58,966
Well, I could use you.

403
00:30:10,435 --> 00:30:13,564
- Hey, Bo. No soccer with Zach this mor...
- Hey.

404
00:30:15,482 --> 00:30:17,818
- Oh, my God.
- No, that's okay.

405
00:30:17,943 --> 00:30:19,862
- Oh, no, no, no. I'm so sorry.
- Sierra.

406
00:30:19,945 --> 00:30:23,949
- I can't believe I just said that.
- Sierra, look at me. Sierra?

407
00:30:24,074 --> 00:30:26,160
Zach will be fine, okay?

408
00:30:26,285 --> 00:30:28,162
- Okay.
- All right?

409
00:30:33,792 --> 00:30:36,336
Goddamn it.

410
00:30:37,796 --> 00:30:39,464
Hey!

411
00:30:39,590 --> 00:30:41,175
Hey!

412
00:30:45,137 --> 00:30:47,389
What are you gonna do, hit me too?

413
00:30:52,144 --> 00:30:54,104
Man.

414
00:31:23,675 --> 00:31:26,595
Yeah. That's bullshit, man!

415
00:31:47,658 --> 00:31:51,453
Yeah, Beverly Hills.

416
00:31:51,537 --> 00:31:53,872
Let me have the number for
a Dr. Jennifer Kelley, please.

417
00:32:04,007 --> 00:32:06,260
- Whoa!

418
00:32:12,891 --> 00:32:14,601
Hey!

419
00:32:14,726 --> 00:32:17,479
- Help me!
- I'm comin', man. Hold on!

420
00:32:17,563 --> 00:32:19,898
You got to help me. Please!

421
00:32:20,023 --> 00:32:22,150
Laramie! Oh, God.

422
00:32:22,234 --> 00:32:24,152
Help me! Hurry!

423
00:32:26,572 --> 00:32:29,158
Hurry!

424
00:32:29,241 --> 00:32:31,535
- I'm here.

425
00:32:31,618 --> 00:32:34,288
- Sit up.
- Help me. Reach. Reach! Reach! Reach!

426
00:32:34,413 --> 00:32:37,249
- Give me your hand.
- Hurry up.

427
00:32:37,374 --> 00:32:39,668
- Give me your hand.

428
00:32:39,751 --> 00:32:41,795
What are you trying to do,
kill me?

429
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:44,464
- Shut up and give me your goddamn hand!
- Damn! Oh, my God!

430
00:32:46,884 --> 00:32:49,845
Help me! Please!

431
00:32:49,928 --> 00:32:52,973
Hold on, man.

432
00:32:53,098 --> 00:32:55,559
- Hurry!

433
00:32:55,642 --> 00:32:59,980
Oh, God! You... You think we were up your
ass before? I'm gonna own you now, slick.

434
00:33:00,105 --> 00:33:03,483
- What'd you say?
- Just pull me up!

435
00:33:03,609 --> 00:33:04,943
Pull me up.

436
00:33:06,069 --> 00:33:08,906
Come on. Pull me up. Hurry!

437
00:33:08,989 --> 00:33:13,702
Pull me up! Now! Now!

438
00:34:03,919 --> 00:34:06,922
I'm startin' to feel much more
in control of my anger.

439
00:34:07,005 --> 00:34:09,883
Well, that's quite a leap in progress.

440
00:34:10,008 --> 00:34:12,261
Especially considering your recent tragedy.

441
00:34:12,344 --> 00:34:14,263
Yeah.

442
00:34:14,346 --> 00:34:17,850
Well, I can't let the fact that
four paparazzis nearly killed my family...

443
00:34:17,975 --> 00:34:19,852
affect my behavior, now, can I?

444
00:34:19,977 --> 00:34:21,854
What do you mean by that, Bo?

445
00:34:21,979 --> 00:34:25,858
Well, you asked me to work
on something, and, uh, I did.

446
00:34:25,983 --> 00:34:29,069
Well, surely you must have
some feelings about what happened.

447
00:34:29,194 --> 00:34:31,572
I feel cheated.

448
00:34:32,990 --> 00:34:34,950
I'm angry.

449
00:34:38,162 --> 00:34:40,330
Blessed.

450
00:34:40,414 --> 00:34:42,416
All at the same time.

451
00:34:44,751 --> 00:34:46,670
- What's this?

452
00:34:46,753 --> 00:34:48,630
A journal.

453
00:34:48,714 --> 00:34:52,676
I want you to start recording specific events
that prompt your anger...

454
00:34:52,759 --> 00:34:54,803
and how you dealt with them
in the moment.

455
00:34:54,887 --> 00:34:57,472
Doing this will help you
put a face on your problems.

456
00:34:57,556 --> 00:35:00,851
My problems already
have faces, Dr. Kelley.

457
00:35:00,934 --> 00:35:03,270
Well, then you're moving
in the right direction.

458
00:35:05,230 --> 00:35:08,108
Let this journal become
a sanctuary for you, Bo.

459
00:35:08,233 --> 00:35:10,486
My clients are having
great success with it.

460
00:35:10,569 --> 00:35:12,863
Really?

461
00:35:35,219 --> 00:35:37,054
This shit happens way too often.

462
00:35:37,137 --> 00:35:39,515
This kid never even hit the brakes.

463
00:35:39,598 --> 00:35:42,851
- This guy ain't no kid. He's close to 40.
- They call 'em Rolex riders.

464
00:35:42,935 --> 00:35:45,854
They hang out in Beverly Hills,
wear expensive leathers.

465
00:35:45,938 --> 00:35:48,273
Same guy cuts all their hair.
Pity. He was cute.

466
00:35:48,357 --> 00:35:51,735
Hey, fellas.
Detective Burton, S.I.S.

467
00:35:51,819 --> 00:35:54,738
- You boys mind if I sniff around?
- Knock yourself out, Detective.

468
00:35:54,822 --> 00:35:56,740
Hey, why's Special Investigations...

469
00:35:56,824 --> 00:35:59,243
sending a D-2 down
to a traffic accident?

470
00:35:59,326 --> 00:36:01,745
Well, I heard your victim's name
on the radio.

471
00:36:01,829 --> 00:36:04,206
He was part of a case
that I've been working on.

472
00:36:04,289 --> 00:36:06,917
It's probably nothing.
I just thought I'd look around.

473
00:36:20,097 --> 00:36:21,974
Here you go, sweetie.

